	PART I

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	FORWARD-LOOKING
</FONT>
<A NAME="CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_FORWARDLOOKING">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	This report contains numerous forward-looking statements within the meaning of Section 27A of the Securities Act of 1933 (the &#x201C;Securities Act&#x201D;) and Section 21E of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (the &#x201C;Exchange Act&#x201D;) relating to our shell egg business, including estimated production data, expected operating schedules, expected capital costs and other operating data, including anticipated results of operations and financial condition.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such forward-looking statements are identified by the use of words such as &#x201C;believes,&#x201D; &#x201C;intends,&#x201D; &#x201C;expects,&#x201D; &#x201C;hopes,&#x201D; &#x201C;may,&#x201D; &#x201C;should,&#x201D; &#x201C;plans,&#x201D; &#x201C;projected,&#x201D; &#x201C;contemplates,&#x201D; &#x201C;anticipates&#x201D; or similar words.&nbsp;&nbsp;Actual production, operating schedules, results of operations and other projections and estimates could differ materially from those projected in the forward-looking statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;The forward-looking statements are based on management&#x2019;s current intent, belief, expectations, estimates and projections regarding our company and our industry.&nbsp;&nbsp;These statements are not guarantees of future performance and involve risks, uncertainties, assumptions and other factors that are difficult to predict and might be beyond our control.&nbsp;&nbsp;The factors that could cause actual results to differ materially from those projected in the forward-looking statements include, among others, (i) the risk factors set forth in Item 1A and elsewhere in this report as well as those included in other reports we file from time to time with the Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#x201C;SEC&#x201D;) (including our Quarterly Reports on Form 10-Q and Current Reports on Form 8-K), (ii) the risks and hazards inherent in the shell egg business (including disease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, such as avian influenza
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, pests, weather conditions and potential for recall), (iii) changes in the demand for and market prices of shell eggs and feed costs, (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	iv) our ability to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	predict and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	meet demand for cage-free and other specialty eggs, (v) risks, changes or obligations that could result from our future acquisition of new flocks or businesses, and (vi) adverse results in pending litigation matters.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;Readers are cautioned not to place undue reliance on forward-looking statements because, while we believe the assumptions on which the forward-looking statements are based are reasonable, there can be no assurance these forward-looking statements will prove to be accurate.&nbsp;&nbsp;Further, the forward
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#8209;looking&nbsp;statements included herein are only made as of the respective dates thereof, or if no date is stated, as of the&nbsp;date hereof.&nbsp;&nbsp;Except as otherwise required by law, we disclaim any intent or obligation to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	publicly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	update these forward-looking statements, whether as a result of new information, future events or otherwise.
</FONT>

<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	ITEM 1.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<A NAME="CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_ITEMIBUSINESS">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	BUSINESS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Our Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Cal-Maine Foods, Inc. (&#x201C;we,&#x201D; &#x201C;us,&#x201D; &#x201C;our,&#x201D; or the &#x201C;Company&#x201D;) is the largest producer and marketer of shell eggs in the United States. In fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, we sold approximately 1,0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million dozen shell eggs, which we believe represented approximately 23% of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	domestic shell egg consumption. Our total flock of approximately 3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million layers and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	9.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million pullets and breeders is the largest in the U.S.&nbsp;&nbsp;Layers are mature female chickens, pullets are young female chickens usually under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	18
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	weeks
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	of age, and breeders are male and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	female chickens used to produce fertile eggs to be hatched for egg production flocks.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ompany has one operating segment, which is the production, grading, packaging, marketing and distribution of shell eggs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The majority of our customers rely on us to provide most of their shell egg needs, including specialty and non-specialty eggs. Specialty eggs represent a broad range of products.&nbsp; We classify nutritionally enhanced, cage free, organic and brown eggs as specialty products for accounting and reporting purposes. We classify all other shell eggs as non-specialty products.&nbsp;&nbsp;While we report separate sales information for these types of eggs, there are a number of cost factors which are not specifically available for non-specialty or specialty eggs due to the nature of egg production. We manage our operations and allocate resources to these types of eggs on a consolidated basis based on the demands of our customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We sell most of our shell eggs in the southwestern, southeastern, mid-western and mid-Atlantic regions of the U.S. We market our shell eggs through our extensive distribution network to a diverse group of customers, including national and regional grocery store chains, club stores, foodservice distributors and egg product consumers. Some of our sales are completed through co-pack agreements &#x2013; a common practice in the industry whereby production and processing of certain products is outsourced to another producer.&nbsp;&nbsp;The strength of our position is evidenced by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	having
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	the largest market share in the grocery segment for shell eggs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	e sell shell eggs to a majority of the largest food retailers in the U.S.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We are one of the largest producers and marketers of value-added specialty shell eggs in the U.S.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	For accounting and tax purposes, we classify
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	nu
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	tritionally enhanced, cage-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	free, organic and brown eggs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	as specialty shell eggs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	They
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	have been a significant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and growing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	segment of the market in recent years.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	During our fiscal 2016 an increasing number of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	food service customers,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	large restaurant chains, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	major retailers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, including our largest customers,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	have committed to exclusive offerings of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	cage-free egg
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	by specified future dates. We are working with our customers to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ensure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	a &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	smooth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	transition
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	in meeting their goals, and have been
</FONT>
</P>
<P>

</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

</FONT>

	branded eggs
</FONT>

</FONT>

</FONT>

</FONT>

	&#xAE; brand. We also produce, market, and distribute private label specialty shell eggs to several customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We are a leader in industry consolidation. Since 1989, we have completed eighteen acquisitions ranging in size from 600,000 layers to 7.5 million layers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Despite a market that has been characterized by increasing consolidation, the shell egg production industry remains highly fragmented.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	At December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, 5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	producers, owning at least one million layers, own
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% of total industry layers and the ten largest producers own
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	50
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% of total industry layers. We believe industry consolidation will continue and we plan to capitalize on opportunities as they arise.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Industry Background&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Based on historical consumption trends, demand for shell eggs increases in line with overall population growth, averaging
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	growth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	of about 1% per year.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	I
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	n &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2013 and 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	consumption of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	eggs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	grew
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	approximately 2% per year.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	However in 2015, egg consumption decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	4% over the prior year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	primarily due to a shortage of supply of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	egg products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	According to U.S. Department of Agriculture (&#x201C;USDA&#x201D;), annual per capita
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	U.S.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	consumption varied between 24
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	63
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	eggs, since 2000. In calendar year 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, per capita
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	U.S.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	consumption was estimated to be 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	eggs, or approximately five eggs per person per week.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;Per capita consumption is determined by dividing the total supply of eggs by the entire population in the U.S. (i.e. all eggs supplied domestically by the egg industry are consumed).&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	While the data can vary somewhat from year to year, of eggs produced in the U.S., approximately 55% are sold to retail consumers (e.g. through grocery and convenience stores), approximately 31% are sold as egg products (shell eggs broken and sold in liquid, frozen, or dried form) to institutions (e.g. companies producing baked goods), approximately 9% are sold to food service companies and 5% or less are exported. Our sales are predominately to retail consumers; in fiscal 2016 and 2015, approximately 4% and 3% of our net sales was egg products, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Prices for Shell Eggs
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Shell egg prices are a critical component of profitability
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	for the Company and the industry as a whole
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. We believe the majority of shell eggs sold in the U.S. in the retail and foodservice channels are sold at prices related to the Urner Barry wholesale quotation for shell eggs. We sell the majority of our non-specialty shell eggs at prices related to Urner Barry Spot Egg Market Quotations or formulas related to our costs of production which include the cost of corn and soybean meal.&nbsp;&nbsp;For fiscal 2016, wholesale large shell egg prices in the southeast region, as quoted by Urner Barry, averaged $1.79 per dozen compared to an average of $1.38 per dozen for fiscal years 2012 to 2015.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Egg prices during fiscal 2016 were impacted by the outbreak of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	avian influenza (&#x201C;AI&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	primarily in the upper Midwestern U.S. from April to June 2015, which initially caused a significant reduction in egg supplies and increase in egg prices
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and had a disproportionately large impact on suppliers of egg products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;While the AI outbreak significantly impacted the supply and prices of eggs during fiscal 2016, there were no positive tests for AI at any of our locations.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	According to a USDA report as of June 1, 2016, the number of layers in the U.S. flock was up 10.2% compared to June 1, 2015, but remained 1.6% below the number of layers for June 1, 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;This increase
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, from June 1, 2015 to 2016,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	is due to the repopulation of flocks
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	depleted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	by the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	AI
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	outbreak.&nbsp;&nbsp;The number of chicks hatched from January through May of 2016 was up 9.6% compared to the same period in 2015.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;Market prices for shell eggs have dropped significantly from the historically high levels we experienced at the beginning of this fiscal year.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Urner Barry price index hit a decade-low level during our fourth quarter, before recovering a portion of these declines in recent weeks.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	While retail demand trends for shell eggs have been favorable, there has been demand erosion for egg products and reduced egg exports. Based on USDA reports, the laying flock is expected to increase through the end of calendar 2016, creating more supply and the potential for further price declines.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Egg prices will likely remain volatile and future
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	prices will depend on levels of supply and the recovery of institutional demand for eggs which was adversely impacted as a result of the 2015 shortages caused by AI.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Feed Costs for Shell Egg Production
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Feed is a primary cost component in the production of shell eggs and represents over half of industry farm level production costs. Most shell egg producers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, including us,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	are vertically integrated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	manufacturing the majority of the feed they require for their operations. Although feed ingredients, primarily corn and soybean meal, are available from a number of sources, prices for ingredients can fluctuate and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	affected by weather
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, speculators,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and various supply and demand factors. Our feed prices for fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	5.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% l
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ower than fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The large
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	harvest
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	increased available supplies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	corn and soybean meal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	favorably impacted our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	results, compared to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	the same period of fiscal 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Increased U.S. acreage for both corn and soybeans in 2016 should provide adequate domestic supplies for both of our primary feed ingredients.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Domestic c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	orn supplies could be particularly robust
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	although domestic
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	soybean stocks
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	could be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	negatively impacted by increased exports due to reduced supplies from S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	outh America.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Growth Strategy
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and Acquisitions
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	For many years, we have pursued a growth strategy focused on the acquisition of existing shell egg production and processing facilities, as well as the construction of new and more efficient facilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since the beginning of fiscal 1989, we have completed eighteen acquisitions. In addition, we have built numerous &#x201C;in-line&#x201D; shell egg production and processing facilities as well as pullet growing facilities which added to our capacity.&nbsp;&nbsp;The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	capacity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	increases have been accompanied by the retirement of older and less efficient facilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;The &#x201C;in-line&#x201D; facilities provide gathering, grading and packaging of shell eggs by less labor-intensive, more efficient, mechanical means.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;Additionally, we continue to upgrade and modify our facilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, and invest in new facilities,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to meet
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	changing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	demand as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	many
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	food service
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	customers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, restaurant chains, and retailers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	have committed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to exclusive offerings of cage-free eggs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	over the next several years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	As a result of our strategy, our total flock, including pullets, layers and breeders, increased from approximately 33.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	5 &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million at May
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	3.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million as of May 28
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The dozens of shell eggs sold increased from approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	21
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million in fiscal 20
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to approximately 1,0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

</FONT>

	6
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

	9

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	908.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million in fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We continue to pursue opportunities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to acquire
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	companies engaged in the production and sale of shell eggs.&nbsp;&nbsp;We will continue to evaluate and selectively pursue acquisitions that will expand our shell egg production capabilities in existing markets and broaden our geographic reach. We have extensive experience identifying, valuing, executing, and integrating acquisitions and we intend to leverage that experience in the evaluation and execution of future acquisitions. We will seek to acquire regional shell egg businesses with significant market share and long-standing customer relationships. We believe enhancing our national presence will help us further strengthen our relationships with existing customers, many of whom have operations across the U.S.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Federal antitrust laws require regulatory approval of acquisitions that exceed certain threshold levels of significance, and we are subject to federal and state laws prohibiting anti-competitive conduct.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe our sales of shell eggs during the last fiscal year represented approximately 23% of domestic shell egg sales, making us the largest producer and distributor of shell eggs in the U.S. However, because the shell egg production and distribution industry is so fragmented, we believe there are many acquisition opportunities available to us that would not be restricted pursuant to antitrust laws.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Through exclusive license agreements with EB in several key territories and our trademarked
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Farmhouse&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	4Grain&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	brands, we are one of the leading producers and marketers of value-added specialty shell eggs. We also produce, market, and distribute private label specialty shell eggs to several customers. Since selling prices of specialty shell eggs are generally
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	less
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	volatile
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	non-specialty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	shell egg prices, we believe growing our specialty eggs business will enhance the stability of our margins.&nbsp;&nbsp;We expect the price of specialty eggs to remain at a premium to regular shell eggs, and intend to grow our specialty shell egg business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The construction of new, more efficient production and processing facilities is an integral part of our growth strategy.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any such construction will require compliance with applicable environmental laws and regulations, including the receipt of permits that could cause schedule delays, although we have not experienced any significant delays in the past.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage6"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Shell Eggs
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Production
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Our operations are fully integrated. We hatch chicks, grow and maintain flocks of pullets, layers, and breeders, manufacture feed, and produce, process, package, and distribute shell eggs.&nbsp;&nbsp;We produce approximately 7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% of our total shell eggs sold, with 9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% of such production coming from company-owned facilities, and the other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% coming from contract producers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under a typical arrangement with a contract producer, we own the flock, furnish all feed and critical supplies, own the shell eggs produced and assume market risks. The contract producers own and operate their facilities and are paid a fee based on production with incentives for performance.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We purchase a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	pproximately 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	total shell eggs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	we sell
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	from outside producers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#FF0000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;BACKGROUND-COLOR:YELLOW;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The commercial production of shell eggs requires a source of baby chicks for laying flock replacement. We produce
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	the majority
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	of our chicks in our own hatcheries and obtain the balance from commercial sources. We own breeder
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and hatchery
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	facilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	capable of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	producing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	21.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million pullet chicks per year in a computer-controlled environment. These pullets are distributed to 4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	state-of-the-art laying operations around the southwestern, southeastern, mid-western and mid-Atlantic regions of the U.S. The facilities produce an average of 2.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million dozen shell eggs per day
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. The shell eggs are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	process
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ed,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	grad
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and packag
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	predominantly without handling by human hands. We have spent a cumulative total of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	270.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million over the past five years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	expand and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	upgrad
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	our facilities with the most advanced equipment and technology available in our industry. We believe our constant attention to production efficiencies and focus on automation throughout the supply chain enables us to be a low cost supplier in all the markets in which we compete.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Feed cost represents the largest element of our farm egg production cost, ranging from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	60
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% to 69% of total farm production cost in the last five fiscal years. Although feed ingredients are available from a number of sources, we have little, if any, control over the prices of the ingredients we purchase, which are affected by weather
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, speculators,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and various supply and demand factors.&nbsp;&nbsp;For example, the severe drought in the summer of 2012 and resulting damage to the national corn
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and soybean
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	crop resulted in high and volatile feed costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Increases in feed costs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	un
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	accompanied by increases in the selling price of eggs can have a material adverse effect on our operations.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, higher feed costs can encourage shell egg producers to reduce production, resulting in higher egg prices.&nbsp;&nbsp;Alternatively, low feed costs can encourage industry overproduction, possibly resulting in lower egg prices.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	After the eggs are produced, they are graded and packaged.&nbsp;&nbsp;Substantially all of our farms have modern &#x201C;in-line&#x201D; facilities to mechanically gather, grade and package the eggs produced.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increased use of in-line facilities has generated significant cost savings compared to the cost of eggs produced from non-in-line facilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to greater efficiency, the in-line facilities produce a higher percentage of USDA Grade A eggs, which sell at higher prices.&nbsp;&nbsp;Eggs produced on farms owned by contractors are brought to our processing plants to be graded and packaged. Since shell eggs are perishable, we maintain very low egg inventories, usually consisting of approximately four days of production.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Egg production activities are subject to risks inherent in the agriculture industry, such as weather conditions and disease.&nbsp;&nbsp;These risks are outside our control and could have a material adverse effect on our operations.&nbsp;&nbsp;The marketability of shell eggs is subject to risks such as possible changes in food consumption
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	preferences
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and practices reflecting perceived health concerns.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We operate in a cyclical industry with total demand that is generally steady and a product that is generally price-inelastic.&nbsp;&nbsp;Thus, small increases in production or decreases in demand can have a large adverse effect on prices and vice-versa.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, economic conditions in the egg industry are expected to exhibit less cyclicality in the future.&nbsp;&nbsp;The industry is concentrating into fewer but stronger hands, which should help lessen the extreme cyclicality of the past.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Marketing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Of the 1,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	0
</FONT>

	53.6
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The shell eggs we sell are either delivered to our customers&#x2019; warehouse or retail stores by our own fleet or contracted refrigerated delivery trucks, or are picked up by our customers at our processing facilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We sell our shell eggs at prices generally related to independently quoted wholesale market prices or at formulas related to our costs of production. Wholesale prices are subject to wide fluctuations.&nbsp;&nbsp;The prices of shell eggs reflect fluctuations in the quoted market and changes in corn and soybean meal prices, and the results of our shell egg operations are materially affected by changes in market quotations and feed costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Egg prices reflect a number of economic conditions, such as the supply of eggs and the demand level, which, in turn, are influenced by a number of factors we cannot control.&nbsp;&nbsp;No representation can be made as to the future level of prices.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	According to USDA reports, for the past five years,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	U.S.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	annual per capita
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	egg
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	consumption
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	grew
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	50
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in 20
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	63
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, before dropping back to 253
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We believe the decrease in consumption in 2015 is attributable to a shortage of supply
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and increase
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	d
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shell egg prices
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	caused by a severe outbreak of avian influenza.&nbsp;&nbsp;Looking ahead, w
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	e believe fast food restaurant consumption, high protein diet trends, reduced egg cholesterol levels, and industry advertising campaigns may result in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	increased per
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	capita egg consumption levels;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	however
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	no assurance can be given that per capita consumption will not decline in the future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We sell the majority of our shell eggs across the southwestern, southeastern, mid-western and mid-Atlantic regions of the U.S. We are a major factor in egg marketing in a majority of these states.&nbsp;&nbsp;Many states in our market area are egg deficit regions which are areas where production of fresh shell eggs is less than total consumption.&nbsp;&nbsp;Competition from other producers in specific market areas is generally based on price, service, and quality of product.&nbsp;&nbsp;Strong competition exists in each of our markets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Seasonality.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Retail sales of shell eggs are greatest during the fall and winter months and lowest during the summer months.&nbsp;&nbsp;Prices for shell eggs fluctuate in response to seasonal demand factors and a natural increase in egg production during the spring and early summer. We generally experience lower sales and net income in our fourth and first fiscal quarters ending in May and August, respectively. During the past ten fiscal years,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	wo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	of our first quarters resulted in net operating losses, and during this same period,

	two

	of our fourth quarters resulted in net operating losses.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Egg Products.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;Egg products are shell eggs broken and sold in liquid, frozen, or dried form.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	egg products represented approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% of our net sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	compared with approximately 3% in fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;We sell egg products primarily into the institutional and food service sectors in the U.S.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our egg products are sold through
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	our consolidated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	subsidiaries
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	American Egg Products, LLC located in Blackshear, Georgia and Texas Egg Products, LLC located in Waelder, Texas.&nbsp;&nbsp;Prices for egg products are directly related to Urner Barry quoted price levels.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Competition
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The production, processing, and distribution of shell eggs is an intensely competitive business, which traditionally has attracted large numbers of producers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Shell egg competition is generally based on price, service, and product quality.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
</P>

<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage8"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The U.S. shell egg industry remains highly fragmented but is characterized by a growing concentration of producers. In 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6 &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	producers with one million or more layers owned
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	291
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million total U.S. layers, compared to 2000, when 63 producers with one million or more layers owned 79% of the 273 million total layers, and 1990, when 56 producers with one million or more layers owned 64% of the 232 million total layers. We believe a continuation of the concentration trend will result in reduced cyclicality of shell egg prices, but no assurance can be given in that regard. A continuation of this trend could also create greater competition among fewer producers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Patents and Trade Names
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We own the trademarks
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Farmhouse&#xAE;, Rio Grande&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Sunups&#xAE;, Sunny Meadow&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	4Grain&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. We do not own any patents or proprietary technologies. We produce and market
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Egg-Land's Best
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<SUB STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</SUB>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and Land O&#x2019; Lakes&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	branded eggs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	under license agreements with EB.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe these trademarks and license agreements are important to our business.&nbsp;&nbsp;We do not know of any infringing uses that would materially affect the use of these trademarks, and we actively defend and enforce them.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Government Regulation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Our facilities and operations are subject to regulation by various federal, state, and local agencies, including, but not limited to, the United States Food and Drug Administration (&#x201C;FDA&#x201D;), USDA, Environmental Protection Agency
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	(&#x201C;EPA&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, Occupational Safety and Health Administration and corresponding state agencies. The applicable regulations relate to grading, quality control, labeling, sanitary control and waste disposal. Our shell egg facilities are subject to periodic USDA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, FDA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	EP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	A inspections. Our feed production facilities are subject to FDA regulation and inspections. In addition, we maintain our own inspection program to ensure compliance with our own standards and customer specifications. We are not aware of any major capital expenditures necessary to comply with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	current
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	statutes and regulations; however, there can be no assurance that we will not be required to incur significant costs for compliance with such statutes and regulations in the future.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;In addition, rules are often proposed that, if adopted as proposed, could have the effect of increasing our costs. For example, in April 2016 the USDA Agricultural Marketing Service proposed rules that, if adopted, would change requirements, and increase our costs, for the production of organic eggs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Environmental Regulation.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Our operations and facilities are subject to various federal, state, and local environmental, health and safety laws and regulations governing, among other things, the generation, storage, handling, use, transportation, disposal, and remediation of hazardous materials. Under these laws and regulations, we are required to obtain permits from governmental authorities, including, but not limited to, wastewater discharge permits. We have made, and will continue to make, capital and other expenditures relating to compliance with existing environmental, health and safety laws and regulations and permits. We are not currently aware of any major capital expenditures necessary to comply with such laws and regulations; however, because environmental, health and safety laws and regulations are becoming increasingly more stringent, including those relating to animal wastes and wastewater discharges, there can be no assurance that we will not be required to incur significant costs for compliance with such laws and regulations in the future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 28
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	6, we had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	3,277
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	employees, of whom
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2,649
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	worked in egg production, processing and marketing,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	178
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	worked in feed mill operations and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	450
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	were administrative employees, including our executive officers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	4.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% of our personnel are part-time.&nbsp;&nbsp;None of our employees are covered by a collective bargaining agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;We consider our relations with employees to be good.
</FONT>
</P>

Information concerning corporate governance matters is also available on our website.

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
