<EFX_MARKET_RISK>
<A NAME="FIS_MARKET_RISK"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	ITEM 7A.&nbsp;&nbsp;QUANTITATIVE AND QUALITATIVE DISCLOSURES ABOUT
</FONT>
<A NAME="CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_ITEM7AQUANTITATIVE">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	MARKET RISKS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	COMMODITY PRICE RISK
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our primary exposure to market risk arises from changes in the prices of eggs, corn and soybean meal, which are commodities subject to significant price fluctuations due to market conditions that are largely beyond our control.&nbsp; For example, feed costs, which during fiscal 2016 averaged approximately 60% of our total farm egg production cost, decreased 15.7% per dozen produced year-over-year.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; We are focused on growing our specialty shell egg business because the selling prices of specialty shell eggs are generally not as volatile as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	non-specialty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shell egg prices.&nbsp;&nbsp;The following table outlines the impact of price changes for corn and soybean meal on feed cost per dozen:
</FONT>
</P>

<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:01.84%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;HEIGHT:15.00PT;PADDING:0PT;">

	$
</FONT>

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:05.80%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;HEIGHT:15.00PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;" NOWRAP="NOWRAP">
	25.00&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:37.00%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;HEIGHT:15.00PT;PADDING:0PT;">

	change in the average market price per ton

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We generally do not enter into long-term contracts to purchase corn and soybean meal or hedge against increases in the price of corn and soybean meal.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	INTEREST RATE RISK
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The fair value of our debt
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is sensitive to changes in the general level of U.S. interest rates.&nbsp;&nbsp;We maintain all of our debt as fixed rate in nature to mitigate the impact of fluctuations in interest rates.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under our current policies, we do not use interest rate derivative instruments to manage our exposure to interest rate changes.&nbsp;&nbsp;A 1% adverse move (decrease) in interest rates would adversely affect the net fair value of our debt by $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	300,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	at May
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	28, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a party to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	other material market risk sensitive instruments requiring disclosure.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">

<A NAME="CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_REPORTOFINDEPENDENT">
</A>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Board of Directors and Stockholders
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Cal-Maine Foods, Inc. and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Jackson, Mississippi
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We have audited the accompanying consolidated balance sheets of Cal-Maine Foods, Inc. and Subsidiaries as of May 28, 2016 and May 30, 2015, and the related consolidated statements of income, comprehensive income, stockholders&#x2019; equity and cash flows for each of the years in the three-year period ended May 28, 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our audits also included the consolidated financial statement schedule listed in the Index at Item 15(a).&nbsp;&nbsp;These consolidated financial statements are the responsibility of the entity&#x2019;s management.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our responsibility is to express an opinion on these consolidated financial statements based on our audits.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We conducted our audits in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States).&nbsp;&nbsp;Those standards require that we plan and perform the audits to obtain reasonable assurance about whether the consolidated financial statements are free of material misstatement.&nbsp;&nbsp;An audit includes examining, on a test basis, evidence supporting the amounts and disclosures in the consolidated financial statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;An audit also includes assessing the accounting principles used and significant estimates made by management, as well as evaluating the overall financial statement presentation.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe our audits provide a reasonable basis for our opinion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In our opinion, the consolidated financial statements referred to above present fairly, in all material respects, the financial position of Cal-Maine Foods, Inc. and Subsidiaries as of May 28, 2016 and May 30, 2015, and the results of their operations and their cash flows for each of the years in the three-year period ended May 28, 2016, in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, in our opinion, the related financial statement schedule, when considered in relation to the basic consolidated financial statements taken as a whole, presents fairly in all material respects the information set forth therein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We also have audited, in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), Cal-Maine Foods, Inc. and Subsidiaries internal control over financial reporting as of May 28, 2016, based on criteria established in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2013 Internal Control &#x2013; Integrated Framework
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission, and our report dated July 15, 2016, expressed an unqualified opinion.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Cal-Maine Foods, Inc. and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
<A NAME="CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_NOTESTOFS">
</A>
</P>
<EFX_NOTES_TO_FINANCIAL_STATEMENT>
<A NAME="FIS_NOTES_TO_FINANCIAL_STATEMENT"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	May 28, 2016
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	1. Significant Accounting Policies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Principles of Consolidation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The consolidated financial statements include the accounts of Cal-Maine Foods, Inc. and its subsidiaries (&#x201C;we,&#x201D; &#x201C;us,&#x201D; &#x201C;our,&#x201D; or the &#x201C;Company&#x201D;).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	All significant intercompany transactions and accounts have been eliminated in consolidation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	principally
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	engaged in the production, processing and distribution of shell eggs. The Company&#x2019;s operations are significantly affected by the market price fluctuation of its principal product, shell eggs, and the costs of its principal feed ingredients, corn, soybean meal, and other grains.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ells
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	shell eggs to a diverse group of customers, including national and local grocery store chains, club stores, foodservice distributors, and egg product
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	consumers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	T
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	he Company&#x2019;s sales are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	primarily
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	in the southeastern, southwestern, mid-western
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and mid-Atlantic regions of the United States. Credit is extended based upon an evaluation of each customer&#x2019;s financial condition and credit history and generally collateral is not required. Credit losses have consistently been within management&#x2019;s expectations.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	customers,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Wal-Mart and Sam&#x2019;s Club,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	on a combined basis, accounted for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	28.9%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	25.7%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	28.2%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	of the Company&#x2019;s net sales in fiscal years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Fiscal Year
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company&#x2019;s fiscal year-end is on the Saturday nearest May 31, which was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 28, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 30, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 31, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	for the most recent three fiscal years.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	All three years fiscal years were 52 week years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Use of Estimates
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The preparation of the consolidated financial statements in conformity with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles requires management to make estimates and assumptions that affect the amounts reported in the consolidated financial statements and accompanying notes. Actual results could differ from those estimates.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Cash Equivalents
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company considers all highly liquid investments with a maturity of three months or less when purchased to be cash equivalents. We maintain bank accounts that are insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (&#x201C;FDIC&#x201D;) up to $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	0,00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 28, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	routinely
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	throughout these years, the Company maintained cash balances with certain financial institutions in excess of federally insured amounts
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. The Company has not experienced any losses in such accounts.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company manages this risk through maintaining cash deposits and other highly liquid investments in high quality financial institutions.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We primarily utilize a cash management system with a series of separate accounts consisting of lockbox accounts for receiving cash, concentration accounts where funds are moved to, and several zero-balance disbursement accounts for funding payroll and accounts payable.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	hecks issued, but not presented to the banks for payment, may result in negative book cash balances
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	are included in accounts payable. At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

	May 28, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 30, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, checks outstanding in excess of related book cash balances totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	zero
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$1.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Investment Securities
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Our investment securities are accounted for in accordance with ASC 320, &#x201C;Investments-Debt and Equity Securities&#x201D; (&#x201C;ASC 320&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company considers all of its investment securities for which there is a determinable fair market value and there are no restrictions on the Company's ability to sell within the next 12 months as available-for-sale. Available-for-sale securities are carried at fair value, with unrealized gains and losses reported as a separate component of stockholders' equity.

	, net of tax,

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Investment in Affiliates
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The equity method of accounting is used when the Company has a 20% to 50% interest in other entities or when the Company exercises significant influence over the entity. Under the equity method, original investments are recorded at cost and adjusted by the Company&#x2019;s share of undistributed earnings or losses of these entities. Nonmarketable investments in which the Company has less than a 20% interest and in which it does not have the ability to exercise significant influence over the investee are initially recorded at cost, and periodically reviewed for impairment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Trade Receivables and Allowance for Doubtful Accounts
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Trade receivables are comprised primarily of amounts owed to the Company from customers, which amounted to $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	62.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million
</FONT>

	at

	May 28, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	99.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million
</FONT>

	. &nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	They
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	are presented net of an allowance for doubtful accounts of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$727,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 28, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	513,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 30, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. The Company extends credit to customers based upon an evaluation of each customer&#x2019;s financial condition and credit history. Although credit risks associated with our customers are considered minimal, we routinely review our accounts receivable balances and make provisions for probable doubtful accounts. In circumstances where management is aware of a specific customer&#x2019;s inability to meet its financial obligations to us (e.g., bankruptcy filings), a reserve is recorded to reduce the receivable to the amount expected to be collected. For all other customers, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	recognize reserves for bad debt
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	based on the length of time the receivables are past due, generally
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	% for amounts more than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	60
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	days past due. Collateral is generally not required. Credit losses have consistently been within management&#x2019;s expectations. At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	both
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 28, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 30, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	customers accounted for approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	29%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	24%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

	of the Company&#x2019;s trade accounts receivable
</FONT>

	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Inventories
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Inventories of eggs, feed, supplies and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	livestock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	are valued principally at the lower of cost (first-in, first-out method) or market.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The cost associated with flocks, consisting principally of chick purchases, feed, labor, contractor payments and overhead costs, are accumulated during a growing period of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	22
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	weeks. Flock costs are amortized to cost of sales over the productive lives of the flocks, generally
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	years. Flock mortality is charged to cost of sales as incurred.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company does not disclose the gross cost and accumulated amortization with respect to its flock inventories since this information is not utilized by management in the operation of the Company.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	44
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage45"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Property, Plant and Equipment
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Property, plant and equipment are stated at cost. Depreciation is provided by the straight-line method over the estimated useful lives, which are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	years for buildings and improvements and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	years for machinery and equipment. Repairs and maintenance are expensed as incurred. Expenditures that increase the value or productive capacity of assets are capitalized. When property, plant, and equipment are retired, sold, or otherwise disposed of, the asset&#x2019;s carrying amount and related accumulated depreciation are removed from the accounts and any gain or loss is included in operations. The Company capitalizes interest cost incurred on funds used to construct property, plant, and equipment as part of the asset to which it relates
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and is amortized over the asset&#x2019;s estimated useful life.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Impairment of Long-Lived Assets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company reviews the carrying value of long-lived assets, other than goodwill, for impairment whenever events and circumstances indicate the carrying value of an asset may not be recoverable from the estimated future cash flows expected to result from its use and eventual disposition. In cases where expected future cash flows (undiscounted and without interest charges) are less than the carrying value, an impairment loss is recognized equal to an amount by which the carrying value exceeds the fair value of assets. The factors considered by management in performing this assessment include current operating results, trends and prospects, the manner in which the property is used, and the effects of obsolescence, demand, competition, and other economic factors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Intangible Assets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Included in other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	intangible assets are s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	eparable intangible assets
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	acquired in business acquisitions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, which include franchise fees, non-compete agreements and customer relationship intangibles,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	are amortized over their estimated useful lives of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	years.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The gross cost and accumulated amortization of intangible assets are removed when the recorded amounts have been fully amortized and the asset is no longer in use
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	or the contract has expired
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;Included in other long-lived assets are loan acquisition costs, which are amortized over the life of the related loan.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Goodwill
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Goodwill represents the excess of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	the purchase price
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	over the fair value of the identifiable net assets acquired. Goodwill is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	evaluated for impairment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	annually
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	by first performing a qualitative assessment to determine whether a quantitative goodwill test is necessary.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	After assessing the totality of events or circumstances, if we determine it is more likely than not that the fair value of a reporting unit is less than its carrying amount, then we perform additional quantitative tests to determine the magnitude of any impairment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Accrued Self Insurance
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We use a combination of insurance and self-insurance mechanisms to provide for the potential liabilities for health and welfare, workers&#x2019; compensation, auto liability and general liability risks. Liabilities associated with our risks retained are estimated, in part, by considering claims experience, demographic factors, severity factors and other actuarial assumptions.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Dividends
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Cal-Maine pays a dividend to shareholders of its Common Stock and Class A Common Stock on a quarterly basis for each quarter for which the Company reports net income computed in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles in an amount equal to one-third (1/3) of such quarterly income. Dividends are paid to shareholders of record as of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	60
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-SIZE:6PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	day following the last day of such quarter, except for the fourth fiscal quarter.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the fourth quarter, the Company will pay dividends to shareholders of record on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	65
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-SIZE:6PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	day after the quarter end. Dividends are payable on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-SIZE:6PT;VERTICAL-ALIGN:SUPER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	day following the record date. Following a quarter for which the Company does not report net income, the Company will not pay a dividend for a subsequent profitable quarter until the Company is profitable on a cumulative basis computed from the date of the last quarter for which a dividend was paid.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	D
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ividends payable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	zero
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$15.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 28, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	May 30, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, respectively
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	These amounts
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	represent accrued unpaid dividends applicable to the Company&#x2019;s fourth quarter net income for each fiscal year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Treasury Stock
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Treasury stock purchases are accounted for under the cost method whereby the entire cost of the acquired stock is recorded as treasury stock.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The grant of restricted stock through the Company&#x2019;s share-based compensation plans is funded through the issuance of treasury stock.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Gains and losses on the subsequent reissuance of shares in accordance with the Company&#x2019;s share-based compensation plans are credited or charged to paid-in capital in excess of par value using the average-cost method.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Revenue Recognition and Delivery Costs
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company recognizes revenue only when all of the following criteria have been met:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 18.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Persuasive evidence of an arrangement exists;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 18.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Delivery has occurred;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">

	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Sales Incentives provided to Customers
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company periodically provides incentive offers to its customers to encourage purchases. Such offers include current discount offers (e.g., percentage discounts off current purchases), inducement offers (e.g., offers for future discounts subject to a minimum current purchase), and other similar offers. Current discount offers, when accepted by customers, are treated as a reduction to the sales price of the related transaction, while inducement offers, when accepted by customers, are treated as a reduction to sales price based on estimated future redemption rates. Redemption rates are estimated using the Company&#x2019;s historical experience for similar inducement offers. Current discount and inducement offers are presented as a net amount in &#x2018;&#x2018;Net sales.&#x2019;&#x2019;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Income Taxes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Income taxes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	provided using the liability method. Deferred income taxes reflect the net tax effects of temporary differences between the carrying amounts of assets and liabilities for financial reporting purposes and the amounts used for income tax purposes.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company&#x2019;s policy with respect to evaluating uncertain tax positions is based upon whether management believes it is more likely than not the uncertain tax positions will be sustained upon review by the taxing authorities.&nbsp;&nbsp;The tax positions must meet the more-likely-than-not recognition threshold with consideration given to the amounts and probabilities of the outcomes that could be realized upon settlement using the facts, circumstances and information at the reporting date.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company will reflect only the portion of the tax benefit that will be sustained upon resolution of the position and applicable interest on the portion of the tax benefit not recognized. The Company shall initially and subsequently measure the largest amount of tax benefit that is greater than 50% likely of being realized upon settlement with a taxing authority that has full knowledge of all relevant information.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Based upon management&#x2019;s assessment, there are no uncertain tax positions expected to have a material impact on the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Stock Based Compensation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We account for share-based compensation in accordance with ASC 718, &#x201C;Compensation-Stock Compensation&#x201D; (&#x201C;ASC 718&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;ASC 718 requires all share-based payments to employees, including grants of employee stock options, restricted stock and performance-based shares to be recognized in the income statement based on their fair values. ASC 718 requires the benefits of tax deductions in excess of recognized compensation cost to be reported as a financing cash flow.&nbsp;&nbsp;See Note 11: Stock Compensation Plans for more information.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Net Income per Common Share
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Basic net income per share is based on the weighted average common and Class A shares outstanding. Diluted net income per share includes any dilutive effects of stock options outstanding and unvested restricted shares.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Basic net income per share was calculated by dividing net income by the weighted-average number of common and Class A shares outstanding during the period.&nbsp;&nbsp;Diluted net income per share was calculated by dividing net income by the weighted-average number of common shares outstanding during the period plus the dilutive effects of stock options and unvested restricted shares.&nbsp;&nbsp;The computations of basic net income per share and diluted net income per share are as follows
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	(in thousands)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	:
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;OVERFLOW: HIDDEN;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="MIDDLE" STYLE="WIDTH:12.92%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:2PT DOUBLE #000000 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;HEIGHT:1.00PT;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2.27&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="MIDDLE" STYLE="WIDTH:56.00%;HEIGHT:1.00PT;PADDING:0PT;">

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Contingencies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Certain conditions may exist as of the date the financial statements are issued that may result in a loss to the Company but which will only be resolved when one or more future events occur or fail to occur. The Company&#x2019;s management and its legal counsel assess such contingent liabilities, and such assessment inherently involves an exercise of judgment. In assessing loss contingencies related to legal proceedings that are pending against the Company or unasserted claims that may result in such proceedings, the Company&#x2019;s legal counsel evaluates the perceived merits of any legal proceedings or unasserted claims as well as the perceived merits of the amount of relief sought or expected to be sought therein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	If the assessment of a contingency indicates it is probable that a material loss has been incurred and the amount of the liability can be estimated, the estimated liability would be accrued in the Company&#x2019;s financial statements. If the assessment indicates a potentially material loss contingency is not probable, but is reasonably possible, or is probable but cannot be estimated, then the nature of the contingent liability, together with an estimate of the range of possible loss if determinable and material, would be disclosed. Loss contingencies considered remote are generally not disclosed unless they involve guarantees, in which case the nature of the guarantee would be disclosed.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	expenses the costs of litigation as they are incurred.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
</P>

<A NAME="eolPage48"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#CALM-20160528X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Impact of Recently Issued Accounting Standards
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In May 2014,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	the Financial Accounting Standards Board (&#x201C;FASB&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	issued Accounting Standard Update No. 2014-09,&nbsp;Revenue from Contracts with Customers&nbsp;(ASU 2014-09). The standard provides companies with a single model for use in accounting for revenue arising from contracts with customers and supersedes current revenue recognition guidance, including industry-specific revenue guidance. The core principle of the model is to recognize revenue when control of the goods or services transfers to the customer in an amount that reflects the consideration that is expected to be received for those goods or services.&nbsp;&nbsp;In August 2015, FASB issued ASU 2015-14 which deferred the effective date of ASU 2014-09 until annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2017. Early adoption is not permitted. The guidance permits companies to either apply the requirements retrospectively to all prior periods presented, or apply the requirements in the year of adoption, through a cumulative adjustment. The Company does not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	expect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ASU 2014-09
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to have a material impact
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	on the consolidated financial statement presentation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In November 2015, the FASB issued A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	SU
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2015-17,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Income Taxes &#x2013; Balance Sheet Classification of Deferred Taxes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The purpose of the standard is to simplify the presentation of deferred taxes on a classified balance sheet.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under current GAAP, deferred income tax assets and liabilities are separated into current and noncurrent amounts in the balance sheet.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendments in ASU 2015-17 require that all deferred tax assets and liabilities be classified as noncurrent in the balance sheet.&nbsp;&nbsp;ASU 2015-17 is effective for annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2016, and interim periods within those annual periods.&nbsp;&nbsp;Early applica
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	tion is permitted.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company adopted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ASU 2015-17
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	during the fourth quarter of fiscal 2016 and retrospectively applied it to all reported periods.&nbsp;&nbsp;Adoption of ASU 2015-17 impacted our previously reported current ratio for fiscal 2015 by increasing it from 3.86 as reported in the prior year to 5.01 as reported in this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	report
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In February 2016, the FASB issued ASU 2016-02,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Leases
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The purpose of the standard is to improve transparency and comparability related to the accounting and reporting of leasing arrangements.&nbsp;&nbsp;The guidance will require balance sheet recognition for assets and liabilities associated with rights and obligations created by leases with terms greater than twelve months.&nbsp;&nbsp;ASU 2016-02 is effective for annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2018, and interim periods within those annual periods.&nbsp;&nbsp;Early adoption is permitted.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company is currently evaluating the impact of ASU 2016-02 on its financial statements and presentation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In March 2016, the FASB issued ASU 2016-09,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Improvements to Employee Share-Based Compensation Accounting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. ASU
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	-09 requires that excess tax benefits are recorded on the income statement as opposed to additional paid-in-capital, and treated as an operating activity on the statement of cash flows. ASU 2016-09 also allows companies to make an accounting policy election to either estimate the number of awards that are expected to vest or account for forfeitures when they occur. ASU 2016-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	09
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	is effective for annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2017 with early adoption permitted.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company does not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	expect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	ASU 2016-09
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to have a material impact
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	on the consolidated financial statement presentation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2.&nbsp;&nbsp;Acquisition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Effective
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	March 1, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, the Company purchased our joint venture partner&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	interest in Delta Egg Farm, LLC (&#x201C;Delta Egg&#x201D;) for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$17.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company previously owned
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	of Delta Egg through a joint venture with Moark, LLC.&nbsp;&nbsp;In conjunction with the acquisition, the Company recognized a non-recurring, non-cash gain of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$4.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million for the excess in purchase price over the carrying value of the 50% investment in the unconsolidated joint venture.&nbsp;&nbsp;This gain was recorded in &#x201C;Other Income&#x201D; in the Company&#x2019;s Consolidated Statements of Income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	for fiscal 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The gain is non-taxable, and therefore resulted in a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$1.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million reduction to the Company&#x2019;s income tax expense for fiscal 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the Company recorded a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$3.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million decrease to deferred income tax liabilities related to the outside basis of our equity investment in Delta Egg.&nbsp;&nbsp;Delta Egg&#x2019;s assets include a feed mill and a production complex with capacity for approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	1.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million laying hens near Delta, Utah, as well as an organic complex with capacity for approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	400,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	laying hens near Chase, Kansas.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The results of the Company&#x2019;s operation of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	se
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	assets are included in the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements since the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	respective
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	of acquisition.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Included in the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements for fiscal 2014 are revenues and net income from Delta Egg of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$4.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$1.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	million, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;Prior to the acquisition date the Company&#x2019;s 50% share of net income was recorded &#x201C;Equity in income of affiliates&#x201D;.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
